1. Find Your Docker Username

Go to Docker Hub

👉 Steps:
Login to your account
Look at top-right corner (profile icon)
You’ll see your username

👉 Example:

nithiyak

Use this for:

DOCKER_USERNAME
🔑 2. Create Docker Access Token (IMPORTANT)
👉 Steps:
Go to Docker Hub
Click your profile icon (top-right)
Click Account Settings
Go to Security tab
Click New Access Token
👉 Fill like this:
Token name → github-actions
Permissions → Read & Write

Click ✅ Generate

⚠️ VERY IMPORTANT

👉 Copy the token immediately
(It will look like this 👇)

dckr_pat_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
🔐 3. Where to Use It

Back in GitHub secrets page:

👉 Add:
Secret 1:
Name: DOCKER_USERNAME
Value: your username
Secret 2:
Name: DOCKER_PASSWORD
Value: paste the token


Step 3: Save & Push to GitHub

Run this in your terminal:

git add .
git commit -m "Added CI pipeline"
git push
🚀 Step 4: What Happens Next

As soon as you push:

✔ GitHub detects .github/workflows/docker-publish.yml
✔ It automatically runs the pipeline
✔ Builds Docker image
✔ Pushes it to Docker Hub

👀 Step 5: Check Output
👉 On GitHub
Go to Actions tab
You’ll see:
🟡 Running
🟢 Success (green)
👉 On Docker Hub
Your repo will have:
python-app:latest

structure   .github/workflows/docker-publish.yml
